ğŸš€ Features

Add Note â€“ Create new notes with titles and categories.

View/Update Note â€“ Edit existing notes.

Delete Note â€“ Remove notes with confirmation.

Search & Filter â€“ Search by title/content and filter by category.

Categories â€“ Create and delete categories for organizing notes.

Find & Replace â€“ Text editor support for find-and-replace in notes.


ğŸ”Œ APIs Overview

| File                   | Description                                               |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| `api/index.php`        | Redirects to homepage                                     |
| `delete-note.php`      | Deletes a note from the homepage (`../index.php`)         |
| `fetch-categories.php` | Fetches & deletes categories on `../pages/categories.php` |
| `get-notes.php`        | Fetches all notes for `../index.php`                      |
| `save-notes.php`       | Saves notes from `../add.php`                             |
| `update-note.php`      | Updates notes from `../edit.php`                          |
| `update-title.php`     | Updates note titles from `../index.php`                   |


ğŸ§  JavaScript Overview

| File                | Used In                            | Description                                              |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `category.js`       | `index.php`, `add.php`, `view.php` | Handles category dropdowns                               |
| `close-btn.js`      | `add.php`, `view.php`              | Closes the note editor without saving                    |
| `fetch-category.js` | `categories.php`                   | Fetches and deletes categories                           |
| `find-replace.js`   | `add.php`, `edit.php`              | Find & replace functionality for text editor             |
| `notes.js`          | `index.php`                        | Fetch/search/filter notes, handle modals for edit/delete |
| `save-notes.js`     | `add.php`                          | Triggers modals to save notes                            |


ğŸ›  Database

SQL schema included in db.sql

Contains tables for:

Notes

Categories

Relationships between them (if normalized)



ğŸ Getting Started

Import db.sql into your MySQL database.

Configure database connection in your backend files (if needed).

Open index.php in your browser to get started.



ğŸ“Œ Notes

This app uses plain PHP and JavaScript (no frameworks).

Make sure to run it in a local server environment like XAMPP, WAMP, or any LAMP stack.

Ensure fetch, POST, and GET requests are properly handled in your server










api/
index.php - redirects to homepage 
delete-note.php - api to delete note from ../index.php page
fetch-categories.php - api to fetch & delete categories in the ../pages/categories.php page
get-notes.php - api to fetch note to the ../index.php page
save-notes.php - api to save notes in the ../add.php page
update-note.php - api to update note in the ../edit.php page
update-title.php - api to update note title in ../index.php page

css/
style.css

js/
category.js - JavaScript functionality for category dropdown selection in ../index.php, add.php and view.php
close-btn.js - JavaScript functionality for exiting add.php and view.php without saving
fetch-category.js - fetch & delete category in ../pages/categories.php using the fetch-category.php api
find-replace.js - JavaScript functionality for text editor, finding and replacing text in the editor
notes.js - fetches notes in the ../index.php page, searching & filtering according to category using the get-note.php api, triggers modals to update note in edit.php  in the ../index.php page using the update-title.php api, trigger modals to delete note from the ../index.php page using the delete-title.php api
save-notes.js - JavaScript functionality to trigger modals to save note in add.php using the save-note.php aspi

pages/
index.php - redirects to homepage
add.php - add new note
view.php - view and update existing note
categories.php - add/delete category

db.sql - DB Schema
index.php - homepage


